# EF Core - Guia de Migraciones para {{ project_name }}

## Paquetes NuGet requeridos

```bash
dotnet add {{ project_name }}.Infrastructure package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore
dotnet add {{ project_name }}.Infrastructure package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.SqlServer
dotnet add {{ project_name }}.Infrastructure package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Tools
dotnet add {{ project_name }}.API package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Design
```

## Configurar en Program.cs

```csharp
builder.Services.AddDbContext<{{ project_name }}DbContext>(options =>
    options.UseSqlServer(
        builder.Configuration.GetConnectionString("Default"),
        sql => sql.MigrationsAssembly("{{ project_name }}.Infrastructure")));
```

## Comandos de migracion

```bash
# Crear migracion inicial
dotnet ef migrations add InitialCreate \
    --project src/{{ project_name }}.Infrastructure \
    --startup-project src/{{ project_name }}.API

# Aplicar a la base de datos
dotnet ef database update \
    --project src/{{ project_name }}.Infrastructure \
    --startup-project src/{{ project_name }}.API

# Ver migraciones pendientes
dotnet ef migrations list \
    --project src/{{ project_name }}.Infrastructure \
    --startup-project src/{{ project_name }}.API
```

## Notas de configuracion

- DbContext: `{{ project_name }}DbContext`
- Schema por defecto: `{{ db_schema }}`
- Auditoria automatica: {{ use_auditing }}
- Soft Delete: {{ use_soft_delete }}
- Connection String key: `Default`

